1. Project Overview
This project compares the performance of two RPL objective functions, OF0 and MRHOF, across small (10 nodes), medium (20 nodes), and large (30 nodes) IoT network scenarios. 
Each scenario was simulated using COOJA on Contiki-NG and repeated five times. Four performance metrics were measured, which are Packet Delivery Ratio, End-to-End Delay, Energy Consumption, and Control Overhead.

2. Repository Contents

rpl_client.c   -- Firmware for client motes. Sends UDP data packets containing a node ID, sequence number, and timestamp to the root, and tracks total packets sent and energy consumed. 
root.c         --Firmware for the RPL root mote. Initialises the DODAG root, runs a UDP server on port 5678, and computes end-to-end delay and total packets received. Prints a final summary at the end of each run. 
project_conf.h --Contiki-NG project configuration. Used to switch the routing metric between OF0 and MRHOF for each scenario. 
parse_log.py   --Python script that parses the exported COOJA mote output log and calculates PDR, average delay, energy consumption, and control overhead. 

